    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen `nvim_out_write` is sent via RPC, the message is truncated in the display. The message still appears properly in `:messages`. If this behavior is intended it should be documented (and would ideally be configurable).\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open Neovim with an 80 column width (verify with `set columns?`)\r\n2. `let m = \"This is a very long string. This is a very long string. This is a very long string.\\n\"`\r\n3. `call nvim_out_write(m)`\r\n4. Observe that the entire string is outputted (and the hit-enter prompt appears)\r\n5. `let @+ = v:servername`\r\n6. Open a new Neovim instance (make sure the original is still 80 columns wide). Follow the remaining steps in the new one.\r\n7. `let sock = sockconnect(\"pipe\", @+, { \"rpc\": 1 })`\r\n8. `let m = \"This is a very long string. This is a very long string. This is a very long string.\\n\"`\r\n9. `call rpcrequest(sock, \"nvim_out_write\", m)`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe message is not truncated (and the hit-enter prompt appears).\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-19+g339011f59\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nRocky Linux 8.6\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nxfce4-terminal 1.0.4 \r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage",
